article.headline: Canisius 71, Marist 56
article.story: BUFFALO, N.Y. -- Julius Coles scored 18 points and Frank Turner had a double-double to lead Canisius to a 71-56 win over Marist on Friday night. Turner finished with 16 points, 10 rebounds and seven rebounds for the Golden Griffins (12-14, 7-8 Metro Atlantic Athletic Conference). Tomas Vazquez-Simmons also had a double-double with 10 points and 11 rebounds. Greg Logins scored 16 points for Canisius, which jumped out to a 17-2 lead in the first half after Turner's tip-in. The Red Foxes (1-24, 1-14) cut the Golden Griffins' margin to six at halftime. But Marist would no closer as Canisius pulled away in the second half, pushing their lead to 20 points on Logins' 3-pointer with 10:06 left. The Golden Griffins took a 64-39 lead -- their largest of the game -- on a three-point play by Turner. Candon Rusin led Marist with 17 points, Korey Bauer had 14 and Devin Price added 12.
